{"word":"ἐνάπτω","slug":"ἐνάπτω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐνάπτω</b></el> <el>(<a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <el>ψω</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to bind on</i> or <i>to</i> a person, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>ἐνῆμμαι</el>, of persons, <i>to be fitted with, clad in</i>, <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a>, <el>λεοντέας ἐναμμένοι</el> (ionic for <el>ἐνημμ-</el>) <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to kindle, set on fire</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}